We have a few lyric odes from CatuHus3 but whether they had less circulation, or were less formally published in books, they are not considered to interfere, by their simple priority of time, with Horace's claim of being the first introducer into Italy of the AEolian strains.

The Epistles are probably, of all Horace's works, the most admired 3 and they are those which seem to place us most at home with the author, and to give the most pleasing reflex of his character.
